</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8B88F79648A80C11DF44A4D2D7D925CB" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="93C276BE9BC049F15040F026D107EFD2" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FC009EB176E88C1B5C81DFE1F21A3E0A" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">
Description of female: 
<bibRefCitation id="A785F976E58DE07EEA46D63E4B8BE3CF" author="Ebmer, AW" journalOrPublisher="Linzer Biologische Beitraege" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" pagination="469 - 506" refId="B35" refString="Ebmer, AW, 1980. Asiatische Halictidae (Apoidea, Hymenoptera). Linzer Biologische Beitraege 12 (2): 469 - 506" title="Asiatische Halictidae (Apoidea, Hymenoptera)." volume="12" year="1980">Ebmer 1980</bibRefCitation>
: 493, Figs 
<figureCitation id="637F9A5EE744338D7C1FD846719A4742" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Halictus fulvitarsis Morawitz, 1876, holotype, female A habitus, lateral view and labels B metasoma, dorsal view C head, frontal view D mesosoma, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.994.58441.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/476411" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">12</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="EF2435A314380D0B062D0696B5EE7AC1" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Halictus fuscicollis Morawitz, 1876, lectotype, female A habitus, lateral view and labels B head, frontal view C mesosoma, dorsal view D metasoma, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.994.58441.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/476412" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">13</figureCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName id="3B6FD367E78F758E17B1A49786A99980" authorityName="Ebmer" authorityYear="1980" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lasioglossum melan" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melan">
<emphasis id="0274D0FF9B127CBFDABED230EEEF9251" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Lasioglossum melan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Ebmer, 1980 (synonymised by 
<bibRefCitation id="C142AD284CBC0ABB4FB6F65FF68647B9" author="Ebmer, AW" journalOrPublisher="Linzer Biologische Beitraege" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" pagination="365 - 430" refId="B43" refString="Ebmer, AW, 1998. Asiatische Halictidae - 7. Neue Lasioglossum -Arten mit einer Uebersicht der Lasioglossum s. str.-Arten der nepalischen und yunnanischen Subregion, sowie des noerdlichen Zentral-China (Insecta: Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Halictidae: Halictinae). Linzer Biologische Beitraege 30 (1): 365 - 430" title="Asiatische Halictidae - 7. Neue Lasioglossum - Arten mit einer Uebersicht der Lasioglossum s. str. - Arten der nepalischen und yunnanischen Subregion, sowie des noerdlichen Zentral-China (Insecta: Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Halictidae: Halictinae)." volume="30" year="1998">Ebmer 1998</bibRefCitation>
: 382).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="90B30E4B8DCC1800CDAE519478D38E23" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">
The lectotype designations by 
<bibRefCitation id="10821ED1172D960D201537A1BC3081B8" author="Ebmer, AW" journalOrPublisher="Linzer Biologische Beitraege" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" pagination="469 - 506" refId="B35" refString="Ebmer, AW, 1980. Asiatische Halictidae (Apoidea, Hymenoptera). Linzer Biologische Beitraege 12 (2): 469 - 506" title="Asiatische Halictidae (Apoidea, Hymenoptera)." volume="12" year="1980">Ebmer (1980</bibRefCitation>
: 495) and by 
<bibRefCitation id="C77932ACF062C615723413D9C739D2A9" author="Warncke, K" journalOrPublisher="Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Venezia" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" pagination="67 - 166" refId="B75" refString="Warncke, K, 1982. Beitrag zur Bienenfauna des Iran. 14. Die Gattung Halictus Latr., mit Bemerkungen ueber unbekannte und neue Halictus -Arten in der Westpalaearktis und Zentralasien. Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Venezia 32: 67 - 166" title="Beitrag zur Bienenfauna des Iran. 14. Die Gattung Halictus Latr., mit Bemerkungen ueber unbekannte und neue Halictus - Arten in der Westpalaearktis und Zentralasien." volume="32" year="1982">Warncke (1982</bibRefCitation>
: 91) were unnecessary as the species was described from a single male that was directly written about by 
<bibRefCitation id="F9E3D9F0E78D70FCE578EBB89C7D8E07" author="Morawitz, F" journalOrPublisher="Izvestiya Imperatorskogo Obshchestva Lyubiteley Estestvoznaniya, Anthropologii i Ethnografii" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" pagination="161 - 303" refId="B52" refString="Morawitz, F, 1876. A Travel to Turkestan by the Member-Founder of the Society A.P. Fedtschenko, accomplished from the Imperial Society of Naturalists, Anthropologists, and Ethnographists on a Commission from the General-Governor of Turkestan K.P. von Kaufmann (Issue 13). Vol. II. Zoogeographical Investigations. Pt. V. (Division 7). Bees (Mellifera). Pt. II [Andrenidae]. Izvestiya Imperatorskogo Obshchestva Lyubiteley Estestvoznaniya, Anthropologii i Ethnografii 21 (3): 161 - 303" title="A Travel to Turkestan by the Member-Founder of the Society A. P. Fedtschenko, accomplished from the Imperial Society of Naturalists, Anthropologists, and Ethnographists on a Commission from the General-Governor of Turkestan K. P. von Kaufmann (Issue 13). Vol. II. Zoogeographical Investigations. Pt. V. (Division 7). Bees (Mellifera). Pt. II [Andrenidae]." volume="21" year="1876">Morawitz (1876</bibRefCitation>
: 241).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="663456B11A48BE133B7AD72F81145C8F" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="D1EF790DEF186C0D7D272172B63B80EB" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7AEF9A0B0F3B21307CEF64042878588A" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">
Kazakhstan, Uzbekistan, Tajikistan, Kyrgyzstan, Afghanistan, Mongolia (Hovd) (
<bibRefCitation id="0EA012435FE266093316962AB9E0A46C" author="Pesenko, YuA" journalOrPublisher="Zoosystematica Rossica" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" pagination="133 - 166" refId="B65" refString="Pesenko, YuA, 2006b. Contributions to the halictid fauna of the Eastern Palaearctic Region: genus Lasioglossum Curtis (Hymenoptera: Halictidae, Halictinae). Zoosystematica Rossica 15 (1): 133 - 166" title="Contributions to the halictid fauna of the Eastern Palaearctic Region: genus Lasioglossum Curtis (Hymenoptera: Halictidae, Halictinae)." volume="15" year="2006 b">Pesenko 2006b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
